<p class="reImgeImg"><img src="../../media/165794/new-sukuk.jpg" width="236" height="149" alt="EGP Sukuk"/></p>
<h1 class="CurrentBN">EGP SUKUK</h1>
<p>Islamic Sukuk are the most important savings that Islamic Banks have emerged as alternative to traditional savings. It is a Shari'a compliant certificate used by Clients interested in saving according to Shari'a principles, under <a title="One of the contracts used in Islamic banks to invest deposits where the client gives the bank the authorization to invest his money in Islamic activities for a certain percentage of the capital to be deducted from realized profit">Wakala</a> investment contract.</p>
</div>
            <div class="CurrentContent ">
           
            <div class="clr"></div>
            
            

 <h5>Benefits</h5>
<div class="CurrentRight">
<table border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><a href="../../formeb4d.html?EGP-Sukuk"><img src="../../images/01.gif" width="284" height="188" alt="Apply Now"/></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<div class="What">
<h3>WHAT DO I NEED?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Account opening form</li>
<li>Copy of national ID or passport copy with a valid residence visa (for Non UAEians)</li>
<li>Recent utility bill</li>
<li>Sukuk application request</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<ul>
<li>Islamic Shari'a Compliant</li>
<li>Competitive profit rates</li>
<li>Eligibility for Islamic <a title="Murabaha is defined as a sale at the original price plus profit or a sale at the capital plus a determined profit">Murabaha</a> against the certificate up to 90%</li>
<li>Possibility of profit withdrawal through ATMs 24/7</li>
<li>Possibility of Suk redemption after 6 months for 3 &amp; 5 years Sukuk based on early redemption table</li>
</ul>
<h5>Eligibility:</h5>
<ul>
<li>Offered to UAEians and foreign residents</li>
<li>Offered to minors under the guardianship of their parents</li>
<li>Offered to Enterprises</li>
</ul>
<h5>Features:</h5>
<ul>
<li>Short and medium-term liability product</li>
</ul>
<h5>Duration and currency:</h5>
<ul>
<li>3 years (LE)</li>
<li>5 years (LE)</li>
</ul>
<h5>Types of certificates:</h5>
<ul>
<li>3 years : LE 1000 and their multiples</li>
<li>5 years: LE 1000 and their multiples</li>
</ul>
<h5>Profit calculation based on Islamic Shari'a guidelines:</h5>
<table border="1" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="4">
<tbody>
<tr style="background-color: #eaeaea;">
<td valign="top" style="background-color: #eaeaea; width: 269px;">
<p><strong>Sukuk</strong></p>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="background-color: #eaeaea; width: 168px;">
<p><strong>Rates</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="269" valign="top">
<p>3 years Sukuk with Monthly Profit</p>
</td>
<td width="168" valign="top">
<p>10.75% -10.80%</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="269" valign="top">
<p>3 years Sukuk with Quarterly Profit</p>
</td>
<td width="168" valign="top">
<p>11.00% - 11.05%</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="269" valign="top">
<p>5 years Sukuk Plus with Monthly Profit</p>
</td>
<td width="168" valign="top">
<p>11.2 5% - 11.30%</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li>3 years EGP: monthly and quarterly<br /> Profit is calculated starting first business day of the month following the purchase date and credited to customer's account by first day of each month or quarterly</li>
<li>5 years: monthly<br /> Profit is calculated starting first business day of the month following the purchase date and credited to the customer's account by first day of each month</li>
</ul>


           
            
